A leader of a Congolese rebel group
suspected of being involved in the rape of at least 303
civilians two months ago has been taken into custody, a United
Nations peacekeeping official said.  The chief of staff of the Mai Mai Cheka rebel group was
arrested today, Leo Salmeron, spokesman for the UN forceâ€™s
operations in the North Kivu province, said in a phone interview
